The striker arrived at the stadium to much fanfare, and shook hands with old colleagues as he made his way to the Liverpool dressing room. 

Balotelli then met  the match-day squad  in the dressing room before kick-off.

After watching the match from the directors' box, he  headed back to Liverpool with the rest of the squad on the team coach.

Ready to go: Balotelli trained at Liverpool on Monday as he completed his transfer from AC Milan

Prior to the match, Liverpool boss Brendan Rodgers told Sky Sports that Balotelli would bring 'trouble' to the club, before expressing his admiration for the new signing.

He said: 'But look at the talent. He's at a stage in his career where this is his chance. I've worked with those types of players all my life in youth coaching where I've never had the finished article.

